1) Install apache ou nginx -  sudo yum install httpd24 httpd24-devel
2) Fazer com que apache suba sempre depois da maquina iniciar -  sudo chkconfig httpd on (se precisar subir na mao service httpd start)
3) Instalar GIT - sudo yum install git
#Install Node
4) curl --silent --location https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_4.x | sudo bash
   - Tutorial - https://easyusedev.wordpress.com/2016/02/04/how-to-install-node-js-4-x-in-aws-ec2-instance/
5) sudo yum -y install nodejs
6) sudo yum -y install gcc-c++ make
6) curl --silent --location "https://www.npmjs.org/install.sh" | sudo bash -


7) Atualiza yum - sudo yum update -y
# Install Node Express Framwork
8)sudo npm install express -g
# Install other dependencies that will be used
9) sudo npm install gulp -g
10) sudo npm install bower -g
# Install CodePloy agent
11) wget https://aws-codedeploy-us-east-1.s3.amazonaws.com/latest/install
12) chmod +x ./install
13) sudo ./install auto
# Install pm2 - Keeps processes running
14) sudo npm install pm2@latest -g
#Creat folders where files will be located
15) cd /var/www/html
16) sudo mkdir FOLDER_NAME
# Create virtualHost folder to use content in port 80
17) cd /etc/httpd/conf
18) sudo mkdir virtualhosts
# Create a virtualHost file that will make 

Pegar todas as tarefas rodando no apache - ps -ef
Matar alguma tarefa - kill -9 <num tarefa>


Arquivo para log de deploy - /opt/codedeploy-agent/deployment-root/deployment-logs

Criar uma pasta para o virtual host em cd /etc/httpd/conf
<VirtualHost *:8080>
   ServerName api.meucarreto.com.br
   ServerAlias api.meucarreto.com.br
   ProxyPreserveHost On

   ProxyRequests off

   <Proxy *>
       Order deny,allow
       Allow from all
   </Proxy>

   ProxyPass / http://localhost:3000/
   ProxyPassReverse / http://localhost:3000/

</VirtualHost>